            p.
              Hello and welcome to my website, which is a portfolio of my programming projects. The site includes presentations of the most interesting applications that I have had the pleasure of creating. Each of them consists of an image that can be enlarged by clicking on, and a brief description. Below the graphics, there are panels providing information about the technology used in the program, including a link to the source code on GitHub, a link to the website if it is a web application, and in the case of two games written in C++, a hyperlink to download the program.
            p.
              I am an amateur programmer. My dream is to get paid employment in the IT industry, although I am aware that starting a career after forty is extremely challenging. I am self-taught in coding, which can be a tough and tedious challenge at times. Fortunately, tutorials, forums, and ChatGPT make the process easier. Coding forums are an interesting phenomenon, reflecting the community of programmers. When I couldn't find a solution to a problem someone else was facing, I asked a question myself. I received a response within 24 hours, and each time it was useful and, moreover, written in a polite tone. I have come to realize that programmers form a helpful community. Assisting in solving someone else's problem, in my opinion, can be an opportunity to develop skills for the person responding to questions. As I mentioned, my path as a self-taught programmer was not always rosy. Sometimes it involved hours of analyzing code, dozens of Google or ChatGPT queries. However, I can proudly say that I never gave up, and I solved every problem independently or with assistance. Programming has definitely taught me, in addition to analytical thinking, perseverance, and consistency in reaching goals.
            p.
              I began my coding adventure during my studies at the Faculty of Automotive and Construction Machinery at the Warsaw University of Technology, majoring in mechatronics. As an electromechanic, I decided to develop a career in the field of designing automation systems. The first languages I encountered in the Computer Techniques course were C++ and LabView. I remember how much satisfaction I got from creating projects during classes or as part of homework assignments. LabView is an incredibly interesting tool. The graphical environment of this language allows the creation of applications for measuring physical quantities, analyzing data, and controlling electronic devices. However, the possibilities of LabView are much greater. For example, I managed to write a game of "Poker" in this language. Creating large projects in the form of block diagrams, however, can be burdened with a lack of transparency in this specific code. Therefore, I decided to focus on the classical solution – code in the form of plain text. That's why I chose to write my own projects in C++. One undeniable advantage of this language is the "cleanliness" of syntax, but since it is a low-level programming tool, mastering memory management skills is necessary to fully utilize its capabilities. I considered it not a good choice for learning a language from the start, so I decided to learn Python. The decision turned out to be appropriate in terms of ease of learning, but the computational efficiency for more complex operations and the limited use of this language in job offers for programmers prompted me to change technologies again. I decided to learn JavaScript, which I considered a compromise between C++ and Python. I believe the decision was correct, especially considering the vast possibilities that the internet provides today. This language is characterized by a large number of ready-made libraries and frameworks, which also determines its positive relationship: accessibility - range of applications. I tie my future to JavaScript, but the path to becoming a fully developed programmer is still far away. I must master asynchronous handling first, and only then begin learning a framework, which will make me a true web developer.
            p.
              However, I am full of hope and determination because I love coding. I have always been attracted to fields that require creativity and logical thinking skills. When you visit my website, you will surely notice that the majority of projects are games. Electronic entertainment is something that particularly attracts me as a former gamer. Designing games, especially those operating in real-time, is a significant challenge because a lot happens in them. Physics engines and artificial intelligence in games are areas that greatly interest me. Someone may say that it is not a serious industry, but firstly, today it operates in billions of dollars, and secondly, Elon Musk also started with game development 😊.
            p.
              With this optimistic statement, I send my regards, Artur.
